post_cb({"25170042": {"ParentId": "25169745", "LastEditDate": "2014-08-06T20:58:16.967", "CommentCount": "1", "CreationDate": "2014-08-06T20:56:43.060", "OwnerUserId": "251738", "LastEditorUserId": "827263", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "25170042", "Score": "7", "Body": "<p>In the <code>reserved names</code> standard 17.4.3.1 (and its sub-paragraphs) I can't find anything that prohibits using <code>std</code> as a nested namespace name. It's not a macro, it's not in the global namespace, and it doesn't seem to meet any of the \"external linkage criteria\" that would prohibit it.</p>\n<p>It appears to be legal (although as you note extremely inadvisable).</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2014-08-06T20:58:16.967"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_25169745_25169918_0": {"section_id": 6299, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "length": 13}}, "n3337": {"so_25169745_25169918_0": {"section_id": 6056, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "length": 13}}, "n4659": {"so_25169745_25169918_0": {"section_id": 7808, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "length": 13}}}, "25169918": {"ParentId": "25169745", "LastEditDate": "2014-08-06T20:55:30.663", "CommentCount": "2", "CreationDate": "2014-08-06T20:48:47.257", "OwnerUserId": "2756719", "LastEditorUserId": "2756719", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "25169918", "Score": "4", "Body": "<p>The rule in the standard that makes the <code>std</code> namespace \"special\" is (\u00a717.6.4.2.1 [namespace.std]/p1):</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_25169745_25169918_0\">The behavior of a C++ program is undefined if it adds declarations or\n  definitions to namespace <code>std</code> or to a namespace within namespace\n  <code>std</code> unless otherwise specified.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This only applies to the top level namespace.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2014-08-06T20:55:30.663"}, "25169745": {"CommentCount": "6", "ViewCount": "210", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "321013", "CreationDate": "2014-08-06T20:37:06.993", "LastActivityDate": "2014-08-06T20:58:16.967", "Title": "Is it legal C++ to declare a nested namespace `std`?", "AcceptedAnswerId": "25170042", "LastEditDate": "2014-08-06T20:54:39.770", "Id": "25169745", "Score": "5", "Body": "<p>The <code>std</code> namespace is special in C++, so ...</p>\n<p>Is this legal C++?</p>\n<pre><code>// at global scope\nnamespace mine {\n  namespace std {\n    ...\n  }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>I'd call it insane, but is it allowed?</p>\n<p>A reference (or non-reference) from the Standard would be appreciated.</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><namespaces><language-lawyer>", "OwnerUserId": "321013", "AnswerCount": "2"}});